body:
~~ConnectionManager should definitely check it is only called on one thread~~. Ah its methods are synchronized.
Maybe we should have a ManagedThreadSafe (like ManagedCloseable), and give that the ability to check that it is running in an event loop thread?
@RobAustin I would propose that we give the ability to check if we are running in any event loop thread - @nicktindall's suggestion was we can just set a ThreadLocal when we start a thread from an event loop
